title: 2011 GEORGIA CUP TIME TRIAL TRAINING SERIES
SECCC Championship Weekend 2011
description: The 2011 SECCC Championship Weekend will consist of a individual/team time trial (16.8 miles), criterium (0.71 mile course), and road race (15.5 mile loop) over the weekend of April 16-17.
course:
Saturday morning\'s individual and team time trials will be featured on 1/3 of the road course for a total of 16.8 miles. With rolling hills, it should be one of the faster time trial courses of the season.

Saturday afternoon\'s 0.71 mile (1.1 km) criterium course is the fastest around. We dare you to find a faster racing course within a city next to a university. Anchored near the Mercer Village, Tattnall Square Park looks to set off the fireworks on the start of an unbelievable 2011 SECCC Championship Weekend!

Sunday morning\'s road race will be featured on a 15.64 mile loop located ten miles east of Macon. Featuring 476 feet of elevation gain per loop, the course will be a demanding one for cyclists. With two Category 5 climbs for about one mile in length, the course will be a tough one for sprinters, but is not exactly suited towards climbers either. The most balanced rider will most likely win the road race.
registration: Registration will occur Saturday morning from 7:15am-7:45am at the parking area before the time trial and at the criterium and road race locations (closing 30 minutes prior to each event except for the time trial).
notes: Please refer to the race website: http://secccmercer.blogspot.com for more details.

title: Global Imports Sandy Springs Cycling Challenge
Global Imports Sandy Springs Cycling Challenge Fun
description:
Join us for a full day of family fun at the 4th Annual Global BMW Sandy Springs Cycling Challenge. Riders in the Metric Century Ride will receive a T-Shirt for participating. All proceeds will go to support our POLICE and FIRE departments in Sandy Springs.

After the ride, please enjoy the Track Side Dining, with a variety of Sandy Springs eateries as well as a first class Art Show and a Concert at the finale.
